Dia. 04 Correct Answer
[{\rtf1\ansi\ansicpg949\deff0{\fonttbl{\f0\fnil\fcharset129 \'b1\'bc\'b8\'b2;}}
\viewkind4\uc1\pard\lang1042\f0\fs18
\par Black's descending move at 1 is the maek to win the capturing race.
\par After White 2, Black pushes and cuts with 3 and 5. It is a good sequence to extends Black's liberties.
\par Then Black plays at 7 and wins the capturing race.
\par White can't play at A because of shortage of liberties.
\par
\par }
